This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of internet routing, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of programmable hardware and control plane algorithms, which could be classified under computer architecture and computer systems and control (cs.CR and cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of metrics and optimization techniques, which could be classified under information theory (cs.IT) and robotics (cs.RO).
